`[ExpectedException]` was removed in MSTest v4. Replace it with `Assert.ThrowsExactly<T>` inside the test body:

```csharp
// Before (v3)
[ExpectedException(typeof(InvalidOperationException))]
[TestMethod]
public void MyTest()
{
    myService.DoWork();
}

// After (v4)
[TestMethod]
public void MyTest()
{
    Assert.ThrowsExactly<InvalidOperationException>(() => myService.DoWork());
}
```

**Key details:**

- **Async tests** → use `await Assert.ThrowsExactlyAsync<T>(() => ...)`
- **`AllowDerivedTypes = true`** → use `Assert.Throws<T>` / `Assert.ThrowsAsync<T>` instead (matches derived exception types)
- **Setup code before the throw** → keep it outside the lambda; wrap only the throwing call

The v3 analyzer **MSTEST0006** could have flagged these ahead of time. Want me to apply this fix to your `ValidationServiceTests.cs`?
